
A simple example for setting the program policy as SCHED_EDF:
(The current name for SCHED_EDF in kernel space is SCHED_DEADLINE)

              EDF(deadline) policy             CPU0  Period
               V                                V     V 
$ ./schedtool -E -d 30000   -b 10000    -p 0   -a0  -g50000    -e yes   2>&1 > /dev/null
                  ^ deadline  ^ runtime   ^ priority   ^ execute the yes program
